            <title>[LOG4J2-944] Log4j Flume appender is not adding millisecond to the event headers when the event is logged at 000 milliseconds.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-944</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the event happens at exact 000 milliseconds, then milliseconds is not inserted.&lt;br/&gt;
We are sending the data to Flume  appenders in syslog Format. where it will add headers.  In header  the standard time stamp is in Below Format &lt;br/&gt;
2015-01-06T07:32:43.345-08:00&lt;br/&gt;
But when the event is logged exactly at 000 milliseconds then millisecond  part is missing  as we can see in below code.&lt;br/&gt;
2015-01-06T07:32:43-08:00&lt;br/&gt;
This cause  exception when we process the data including milliseconds.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
